---
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

    <title>Heritage Coastal | Respectful Property Transitions</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Heritage Coastal works with homeowners, families, and estates seeking a respectful, private, and thoughtful transition of coastal properties."
    />

    <style>
      :root {
        --navy: #182536;
        --deep-green: #26382f;
        --cream: #f6f1e7;
        --paper: #fbf8f0;
        --gold: #b79b5b;
        --muted: #6f746d;
        --line: rgba(38, 56, 47, 0.18);
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--deep-green);
        font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
      }

      .page {
        min-height: 100vh;
        background:
          linear-gradient(rgba(24, 37, 54, 0.78), rgba(24, 37, 54, 0.68)),
          url("https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500530855697-b586d89ba3ee?auto=format&fit=crop&w=2200&q=80");
        background-size: cover;
        background-position: center;
        color: white;
      }

      header {
        width: 100%;
        padding: 32px 7vw;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
      }

      .brand {
        letter-spacing: 0.24em;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .nav-note {
        font-size: 15px;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.78);
      }

      .hero {
        padding: 110px 7vw 150px;
        max-width: 980px;
      }

      .eyebrow {
        color: var(--gold);
        letter-spacing: 0.22em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-size: 13px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(46px, 7vw, 86px);
        line-height: 0.98;
        font-weight: 400;
        margin: 0 0 32px;
        max-width: 900px;
      }

      .hero p {
        font-size: 22px;
        line-height: 1.65;
        max-width: 680px;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);
        margin-bottom: 38px;
      }

      .button-row {
        display: flex;
        gap: 16px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
      }

      .button {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 16px 26px;
        border-radius: 2px;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-size: 15px;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      }

      .primary {
        background: var(--gold);
        color: #182536;
      }

      .secondary {
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
        color: white;
      }

      section {
        padding: 92px 7vw;
      }

      .intro {
        background: var(--paper);
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.15fr;
        gap: 70px;
        align-items: start;
      }

      .section-label {
        color: var(--gold);
        letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-size: 12px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: clamp(34px, 4vw, 56px);
        line-height: 1.08;
        font-weight: 400;
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--navy);
      }

      .intro-text p,
      .card p,
      .note p {
        font-size: 19px;
        line-height: 1.75;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin-top: 0;
      }

      .principles {
        background: var(--cream);
      }

      .grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 28px;
        margin-top: 52px;
      }

      .card {
        background: var(--paper);
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 38px;
        min-height: 260px;
      }

      .number {
        color: var(--gold);
        font-size: 14px;
        letter-spacing: 0.16em;
        margin-bottom: 28px;
      }

      h3 {
        font-size: 27px;
        line-height: 1.2;
        font-weight: 400;
        color: var(--navy);
        margin: 0 0 18px;
      }

      .process {
        background: var(--paper);
      }

      .steps {
        margin-top: 46px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      }

      .step {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr;
        gap: 34px;
        padding: 34px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      }

      .step strong {
        color: var(--gold);
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        font-size: 13px;
      }

      .step p {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 20px;
        line-height: 1.65;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .quote {
        background: var(--navy);
        color: white;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 105px 10vw;
      }

      .quote p {
        font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 54px);
        line-height: 1.25;
        max-width: 1050px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        font-weight: 400;
      }

      .contact {
        background: var(--paper);
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 70px;
        align-items: center;
      }

      .contact-box {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 44px;
        background: var(--cream);
      }

      .contact-box a {
        color: var(--navy);
        text-decoration: none;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold);
      }

      footer {
        padding: 34px 7vw;
        background: var(--navy);
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.68);
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 20px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 850px) {
        header,
        footer {
          flex-direction: column;
          align-items: flex-start;
        }

        .hero {
          padding-top: 70px;
        }

        .intro,
        .contact,
        .grid,
        .step {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        section {
          padding: 68px 7vw;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <header>
        <div class="brand">HERITAGE COASTAL</div>
        <div class="nav-note">Private property transitions</div>
      </header>

      <main class="hero">
        <div class="eyebrow">Stewardship • Continuity • Respect</div>

        <h1>For owners considering the next chapter of a cherished property.</h1>

        <p>
          Heritage Coastal works directly with homeowners, families, and estates
          seeking a private, thoughtful, and dignified transition of coastal real
          estate.
        </p>

        <div class="button-row">
          <a class="button primary" href="mailto:info@heritagecoastal.com">
            Start a Private Conversation
          </a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="#approach">Our Approach</a>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>

    <section class="intro" id="approach">
      <div>
        <div class="section-label">Our Belief</div>
        <h2>A home is not merely an asset. It is a record of care.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="intro-text">
        <p>
          Many properties carry decades of family history, neighborhood memory,
          and personal investment. We approach those conversations with patience,
          discretion, and respect.
        </p>

        <p>
          Our role is simple: to provide a clear path for owners who may be
          ready to sell, but do not want pressure, spectacle, or a rushed public
          process.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="principles">
      <div class="section-label">Principles</div>
      <h2>Quiet, direct, and considerate.</h2>

      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <div class="number">01</div>
          <h3>Respect for the owner</h3>
          <p>
            We move at a pace that suits the family, not the market. No hard
            sell. No unnecessary urgency. No public pressure.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <div class="number">02</div>
          <h3>Respect for the property</h3>
          <p>
            Every property has a story. We take time to understand its history,
            condition, setting, and the owner’s hopes for what comes next.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <div class="number">03</div>
          <h3>Respect for privacy</h3>
          <p>
            Conversations remain private. We can discuss options quietly,
            without listing, staging, showings, or neighborhood speculation.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="process">
      <div class="section-label">How It Works</div>
      <h2>A simpler alternative to a public sale.</h2>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <strong>FIRST</strong>
          <p>
            We have a private conversation to understand the property, the
            timing, and whether a direct transaction may be appropriate.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <strong>SECOND</strong>
          <p>
            If there is mutual interest, we review the property carefully and
            provide a clear proposal without requiring repairs, staging, or
            open houses.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <strong>THIRD</strong>
          <p>
            The owner chooses the path and timing. We can accommodate flexible
            closing dates, estate situations, family transitions, and as-is
            sales.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="quote">
      <p>
        We believe the best transactions are not extracted. They are earned
        through patience, clarity, and trust.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contact">
      <div>
        <div class="section-label">Contact</div>
        <h2>Begin with a private note.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="contact-box">
        <p>
          If you are considering a sale, managing an estate, or simply weighing
          options for a coastal property, we welcome a confidential conversation.
        </p>

        <p>
          Email:
          <a href="mailto:info@heritagecoastal.com">
            info@heritagecoastal.com
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer>
      <div>© 2026 Heritage Coastal</div>
      <div>Private acquisitions of coastal homes and legacy properties</div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>